20/06/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Several thousand Croatians gathered in Zagreb's main square on Saturday evening (19 June) to celebrate the European Council's decision to launch accession talks with their country, which is now an official EU candidate. 
To commemorate the event, the government organised an open-air concert featuring the Zagreb Philharmonic and many popular local signers.The event started with Prime Minister Ivo Sanader lifting the EU flag alongside Croatia's one in a symbolic gesture. 
Croatia hopes to join the EU in 2007, together with Bulgaria and Romania. 
According to opinion polls, more than 72 per cent of citizens support the country's EU membership bid. 
(HINA - 20/06/04; EUbusiness - 19/06/04)
